\ Cross-process image round-trip (part 1 of 2): save in this process.
\ Part 2 (131) loads this image in a SEPARATE process invocation.
\ caller's body references other words, so its compiled body holds
\ handler pointers that must survive across process launches.
: square dup * ;
variable counter   42 to counter
: caller square counter + ;
"/tmp/lf-xproc-test.image" save-image
